---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us | SciCalcX Online Computational Suite" description="Discover the mission, technology stack, and computational design behind SciCalcX—the premium open-source online scientific calculator.">
  <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 sm:space-y-8 font-sans">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="text-center md:text-left space-y-1.5 border-b border-brand-border/60 pb-4">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-blue-neon">
        Organization Profile
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-text">
        About SciCalcX<span class="text-brand-blue">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted">
        Designing premium, high-performance web tools for calculations, matrices, calculus, and programming logic.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Intro Card -->
    <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/40 rounded-xl p-6 space-y-4 shadow-xl backdrop-blur-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-white font-mono flex items-center gap-1.5">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-blue-neon"></span> Our Mission
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-brand-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        SciCalcX was founded with a singular purpose: to build the most accessible, high-performance, and visually elegant <strong>online scientific calculator</strong>. Standard browser calculators often suffer from clunky user interfaces, lack of support for multi-line inputs, and precision arithmetic errors. We set out to design a responsive, open-source mathematical environment addressing common engineering requirements directly on the web.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Features Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/30 rounded-xl p-5 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-text font-mono">
          Unified Math Workspaces
        </h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          From basic parenthesized formulas to vector-matrix algebra, integration limits, cubic roots solvers, and coordinate graphing canvas overlays, SciCalcX coordinates your academic workflows under one roof.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/30 rounded-xl p-5 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-text font-mono">
          Interactive Bitboards
        </h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Built with digital developers and systems engineers in mind, our programmer suite features a 32-bit visual bitboard to toggle bits interactively and convert bases in real-time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack details -->
    <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-gray-dark/40 rounded-xl p-6 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-white font-mono flex items-center gap-1.5">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-blue"></span> Built with Modern Architecture
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-brand-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Our core computational engine utilizes state-of-the-art tokenization and Shunting-yard algorithms implemented natively in client-side TypeScript. By running calculations completely client-side, we guarantee latency-free evaluations without round-trip server overhead.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 pt-2 font-mono text-[10px] text-center">
        <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-black p-2 rounded">
          <span class="text-brand-blue-neon block font-bold">Astro 6.0</span> Framework
        </div>
        <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-black p-2 rounded">
          <span class="text-brand-blue-neon block font-bold">Tailwind v4</span> Design Tokens
        </div>
        <div class="border border-brand-border bg-brand-black p-2 rounded">
          <span class="text-brand-blue-neon block font-bold">TypeScript</span> Computations
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
